# Backend Rules

- Use Pydantic models from `app/models/schemas.py` for all request/response types.
- The LangGraph `OnboardingState` TypedDict drives the agent; graph is `classify` → `validate` → `respond` → `check_complete`. Nodes must return the full state.
- `onboarding_validation.py`: Groq/Qwen JSON for `sidebar_caption` + reply quality; heuristic fallback. Repeated nonsense → specialist template (skips Claude).
- `_compile_system_prompt()` fetches from Langfuse first, falls back to `FALLBACK_PROMPT`. Never hardcode prompt changes without updating both.
- Escalation is detected in `check_complete` via `ESCALATION_SIGNALS` phrase list. Add new signals there, always lowercase.
- The `classify_phase` node uses Qwen 3 (via Groq) when `GROQ_API_KEY` is set, with keyword fallback. Qwen 3 returns `<think>` tags — strip them with `_THINK_RE` before parsing.
- NPI service tries live NPPES first (`httpx`, 5s timeout), then mock fallback. Log failures, don't swallow silently.
- `ChatResponse` includes `current_phase`, `needs_escalation`, `sidebar_caption`, `validation_quality` alongside `response`.
- Langfuse tracing uses `langfuse.langchain.CallbackHandler` when keys are set.
